                     <interp inst="t18291029-171-person1360" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of Mr. Thurgood. On Monday, the 28th, the prisoner came, and had four loaves for Mr. Clark.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18291029-171-person1361">
                  EDWARD 
                  HANDS
               <interp inst="t18291029-171-person1361" type="surname" value="HANDS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-171-person1361" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-171-person1361" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a headborough of St. Luke's. I received information, and took the prisoner at a woodshop; I told him what he had been doing - he said he was hungry, and wanted me to take him to his mother; I refused, and took him to the watch-house; he showed me five different places, at which he had sold the loaves.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 10.</p>
